{"TopicId":132718,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Mars 2022","CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-22T17:25:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-22T17:25:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022\\\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacenews.com/nasa-eyes-new-mars-orbiter-for-2022/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://spacenews.com/nasa-eyes-new-mars-orbiter-for-2022/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cb\u003EMars 2022 orbiter\u003C/b\u003E is a concept study by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA\u0022 title=\u0022NASA\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ENASA\u003C/a\u003E to develop a \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars\u0022 title=\u0022Mars\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMars\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Communications_satellite\u0022 title=\u0022Communications satellite\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ecommunications satellite\u003C/a\u003E with a modest mapping capability payload, and propelled by a solar electric \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ion_thruster\u0022 title=\u0022Ion thruster\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eion thruster\u003C/a\u003E.\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-SFN-1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E1\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-Leone-2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E2\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe orbiter is proposed to be launched in September 2022 to link ground controllers with rovers and landers and extend mapping capabilities expected to be lost when the \u003Ci\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_Reconnaissance_Orbiter\u0022 title=\u0022Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMars Reconnaissance Orbiter\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/i\u003E and \u003Ci\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2001_Mars_Odyssey\u0022 title=\u00222001 Mars Odyssey\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2001 Mars Odyssey\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/i\u003E stop functioning.\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-SFN-1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E1\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConcern in NASA is that the currently used relay satellites, \u003Ci\u003E2001 Mars Odyssey\u003C/i\u003E and \u003Ci\u003EMars Reconnaissance Orbiter\u003C/i\u003E, may stop functioning, resulting in the need to press the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MAVEN\u0022 title=\u0022MAVEN\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMAVEN\u003C/a\u003E science orbiter into use as a backup telecommunications relay.\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-SFN-1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E1\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-Leone-2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E2\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-5\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E5\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E However, the highly elliptical orbit of MAVEN will limit its usefulness as a relay for surface operations.\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-Telecom-6\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E6\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_2022#cite_note-nasa20141110-7\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E7\u003Cspan\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis probe will also improve mapping capabilities and telecommunications at mars. Let\u0027s hope this becomes a reality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-22T20:19:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like it. We get to test SEP for a Mars mission, and get a brand new communication satellite that can be used for future missions as well as current ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChrisSpace","CreatedById":140622,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T04:44:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably won\u0027t happen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T05:08:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not? It seems like a pretty reasonable mission to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}